# MJML Renderer API — local requests
# Requires: pnpm start (or node server.mjs) with default PORT=8080
# VS Code / Cursor: REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)
#
# @baseUrl — change if you use another port (Railway: your public URL)
@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8080
#
# Set when the server has MJML_API_TOKEN; leave empty if auth is off
@apiToken =

### GET / — metadata (mjmlVersion, service name)
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### GET /health — probe
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### POST /render — JSON body
POST {{baseUrl}}/render
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-Id: local-http-json-1

{
  "mjml": "<mjml><mj-body><mj-section><mj-column><mj-text>Hello from JSON</mj-text></mj-column></mj-section></mj-body></mjml>"
}

### POST /render — JSON with allowlisted options
POST {{baseUrl}}/render
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mjml": "<mjml><mj-body><mj-section><mj-column><mj-text>Minified-ish</mj-text></mj-column></mj-section></mj-body></mjml>",
  "options": {
    "minify": true,
    "validationLevel": "strict"
  }
}

### POST /render — text/plain
POST {{baseUrl}}/render
Content-Type: text/plain

<mjml><mj-body><mj-section><mj-column><mj-text>Hello plain</mj-text></mj-column></mj-section></mj-body></mjml>

### POST /render — text/mjml
POST {{baseUrl}}/render
Content-Type: text/mjml

<mjml><mj-body><mj-section><mj-column><mj-text>Hello text/mjml</mj-text></mj-column></mj-section></mj-body></mjml>

### POST /render — application/xml
POST {{baseUrl}}/render
Content-Type: application/xml

<mjml><mj-body><mj-section><mj-column><mj-text>Hello XML</mj-text></mj-column></mj-section></mj-body></mjml>

### POST /render — text/xml
POST {{baseUrl}}/render
Content-Type: text/xml

<mjml><mj-body><mj-section><mj-column><mj-text>Hello text/xml</mj-text></mj-column></mj-section></mj-body></mjml>

### POST /v1/render — versioned path (same behaviour as /render)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/render
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mjml": "<mjml><mj-body><mj-section><mj-column><mj-text>Hello v1</mj-text></mj-column></mj-section></mj-body></mjml>"
}

### POST /render — optional Bearer (set @apiToken at top when using MJML_API_TOKEN)
POST {{baseUrl}}/render
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}

{
  "mjml": "<mjml><mj-body><mj-section><mj-column><mj-text>Authed</mj-text></mj-column></mj-section></mj-body></mjml>"
}

### OPTIONS /render — CORS preflight (only relevant when CORS_ORIGIN is set on server)
OPTIONS {{baseUrl}}/render
Origin: http://localhost:5173
Access-Control-Request-Method: POST
Access-Control-Request-Headers: content-type,authorization,x-request-id
